  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>Neurofeedback success (brain activation difference during neurofeedback and baseline blocks)</measure>
    <time_frame>1 day</time_frame>
    <description>This measure will be based on the analysis of participants' fMRI (functional magnetic resonance imaging) data, reflecting brain activation, during exposure to alcohol cues. Neurofeedback success will be defined as significant difference between activation levels (expressed as beta weights of a linear regression model) during the regulation periods compared to baseline. The significance will be determined by a t-test.</description>
  </primary_outcome>
